# Application Module Pattern

Use the application layer for use-case orchestration only.

## Rules

- Organize features by module, then by command/query use case.
- Commands change state.
- Queries read state.
- One command/query should have one handler.
- Handlers should orchestrate, not hold deep business rules.
- Controllers should delegate to application handlers instead of calling repositories directly.

## Preferred Structure

```text
backend/src/Layers/Application/
  Booking/
    Commands/
      CreateBooking/
      ConfirmBooking/
    Queries/
      GetBookingById/
      ListBookingsForApartment/
  Shared/
    Messaging/
```

## Return Rules

- Command handlers should return `Result` or `ResultWithValue<scalar|dto>`.
- Query handlers should return `ResultWithValue<read-dto|list<read-dto>>`.
- Do not return aggregates from application handlers unless there is a strong reason.

## Dependency Rules

- Application handlers may depend on repositories, domain services, and event dispatchers.
- Application handlers should not contain persistence details beyond orchestration.
- Application handlers should dispatch domain events after persistence.
